attacks.name: Rock Tomb

data.flavorText: Known as the Drill King, this Pokémon can tunnel through the terrain at speeds of over 90 mph.

data.flavorText: Long ago it lived in mines, but once the minerals that make up its diet became scarcer, Klefki began appearing in human settlements.

attacks.name: Iron Intake
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.

attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

data.flavorText: With their great intellect and flying skills, these Pokémon very successfully act as the Galar region's airborne taxi service.

data.name: Cufant

attacks.name: High Horsepower
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: If a job requires serious strength, this Pokémon will excel at it. Its copper body tarnishes in the rain, turning a vibrant green color.

data.name: Copperajah

attacks.name: High Horsepower
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: These Pokémon live in herds. Their trunks have incredible grip strength, strong enough to crush giant rocks into powder.

data.flavorText: It can telepathically communicate with people. It changes its appearance using its down that refracts light.

attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It understands human speech and is highly intelligent. It is a tender Pokémon that dislikes fighting.

data.name: Goomy
data.flavorText: Their horns are powerful sensors. As soon as Goomy pick up any sign of enemies, they go into hiding. This is how they've survived.

abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, whenever your opponent tries to attach an Energy card from their hand to a Pokémon, they must flip a coin. If tails, your opponent discards that Energy card instead of attaching it, and this doesn't use up their Energy attachment for the turn.

data.flavorText: Its form of offense is forcefully stretching out its horns. The strikes land 100 times harder than any blow from a heavyweight boxer.

data.name: Sliggoo

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.flavorText: The lump on its back contains its tiny brain. It thinks only of food and escaping its enemies.

attacks.name: Pay Day
attacks.text: Draw a card.

data.flavorText: Its elegant and refined behavior clashes with that of the barbaric Perrserker. The relationship between the two is one of mutual disdain.

data.name: Turtonator

attacks.name: Shell Trap
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack (even if it is Knocked Out), put 8 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Eating sulfur in its volcanic habitat is what causes explosive compounds to develop in its shell. Its droppings are also dangerously explosive.

data.name: Meowth

attacks.name: Pay Day
attacks.text: Draw a card.

attacks.name: Drain Slap
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.

attacks.name: Wild Dive

attacks.name: Double Kick

data.name: Lopunny

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

data.name: Exeggcute
data.flavorText: Though it may look like it's just a bunch of eggs, it's a proper Pokémon. Exeggcute communicates with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.

data.name: Exeggutor

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Each of Exeggutor's three heads is thinking different thoughts. The three don't seem to be very interested in one another.

data.name: Shroomish
data.flavorText: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.

data.name: Breloom

attacks.name: Spore Ball
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Powdery Uppercut
attacks.text: You can use this attack only if this Pokémon used Spore Ball during your last turn.

data.flavorText: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.

data.name: Tropius

abilities.name: Curative Bower
abilities.text: All of your Pokémon that have Grass Energy attached can't be Confused, and if they are already Confused, they recover from that Special Condition.

data.flavorText: Bunches of delicious fruit grow around its neck. In warm areas, many ranches raise Tropius.

data.name: Turtwig
data.flavorText: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

data.name: Grotle

abilities.name: Sun-Drenched Shell
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Grass Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.

data.name: Torterra

attacks.name: Evopress
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage for each of your Evolution Pokémon in play.

data.flavorText: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.

data.name: Burmy
data.flavorText: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

data.name: Wormadam

attacks.name: Matron's Anger
attacks.text: This attack does 10 more damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile.

attacks.name: Leaf Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.

data.name: Mothim

attacks.name: Raid
attacks.text: If this Pokémon evolved from Burmy during this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

data.flavorText: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the Combee hive.

data.name: Cherubi

abilities.name: Lively Fruit
abilities.text: Prevent all effects of attacks from your opponent's Pokémon done to this Pokémon. (Damage is not an effect.)

data.flavorText: The deeper a Cherubi's red, the more nutrients it has stockpiled in its body. And the sweeter and tastier its small ball!

data.name: Karrablast
data.flavorText: Its strange physiology reacts to electrical energy in interesting ways. The presence of a Shelmet will cause this Pokémon to evolve.

data.name: Magmar
data.flavorText: Magmar dispatches its prey with fire. But it regrets this habit once it realizes that it has burned its intended prey to a charred crisp.

data.name: Magmortar

attacks.name: Boltsplosion
attacks.text: If Electivire is on your Bench, this attack does 120 more damage.

data.flavorText: When Magmortar inhales deeply, the fire burning in its belly intensifies, rising in temperature to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

attacks.name: Inferno Wings
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any damage counters on it, this attack does 70 more damage. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness.

data.flavorText: It's one of the legendary bird Pokémon. When Moltres flaps its flaming wings, they glimmer with a dazzling red glow.

data.flavorText: The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.

data.flavorText: If you visit a beach at the end of summer, you'll be able to see groups of Staryu lighting up in a steady rhythm.

data.name: Lapras

attacks.name: Raging Freeze
attacks.text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon during their last turn, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.flavorText: A smart and kindhearted Pokémon, it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.

data.name: Corphish
data.flavorText: No matter how dirty the water in the river, it will adapt and thrive. It has a strong will to survive.

data.name: Crawdaunt

attacks.name: Crab Impact

data.flavorText: A rough customer that wildly flails its giant claws. It is said to be extremely hard to raise.

data.name: Snorunt

attacks.name: Ice Breath
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.flavorText: It can only survive in cold areas. It bounces happily around, even in environments as cold as -150 degrees Fahrenheit.

data.name: Piplup

attacks.name: Bubble
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.flavorText: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

data.name: Prinplup
data.flavorText: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees.

data.name: Empoleon

abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in your discard pile and you have no cards in your hand, you may put this Pokémon onto your Bench. If you do, draw 3 cards.

data.flavorText: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.
